Claude Code project settings that wire the `ctx-context` binary into the tool-use loop: after any `Read`, `Grep`, or `Glob` invocation, it runs `target/debug/ctx-context --hook`, silencing stderr and forcing overall success (`|| true`) so a missing/failing binary never blocks Claude's workflow.

This assumes `ctx-context` has already been built at `target/debug/ctx-context` (debug profile specifically — a release build won't be picked up unless this path is updated); if the build is stale or absent, the hook silently no-ops rather than erroring, so a missing context update after file exploration may go unnoticed. `$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR` is supplied by Claude Code itself, not defined here. Editing the matcher list changes which tool calls trigger context refresh — currently only read-style tools (`Read|Grep|Glob`), not `Edit`/`Write`.